      "text": "We show that in visually guided predator-prey interactions, planning provides a significant advantage, but only on land. During animal evolution, the water-to-land transition resulted in a massive increase in visual range. Simulations of behavior identify a specific type of terrestrial habitat, clustered open and closed areas, where the advantage of planning peaks. [https://www.nature.com/articles/s41467-020-16102-1 nature] [https://www.nature.com/articles/s41467-020-16102-1/figures/1 expand]"
